nit: lowercase? `Pad`
Prefer at least "VALUE".  Maybe you can come up with something more descriptive.
Done
Done
Suggest using something more descriptive than "C" and "CC".  These end up as journald fields.
Done
HEADER?
Done
We don't need function names, I don't think.  These end up being part of the automatic source_location added to the journal.
Done

Definitely don't need this.  source_location is already added.  This seems like a bad debug statement anyhow.  Suggest removing all of these "LINE" debug statements or adding something useful to them.
Done
This was originally a wrap re-direct and not a direct dependency, right?  I don't think you need to include those.

I'm not too good with meson. If you look at the jenkins output from the previous patchsets, there were issues involving the wrap-redirect.

Feel free to push new revisions. Otherwise i can try my luck tomorrow.

Also, it should not be a direct dependency, right?

It's just a subproject wrap. I'm not sure if meson uses them unless required.
Because it's not marked as a dependency in meson.build file.
That's right, it isn't a direct dependency of entity-manager, only of phosphor-logging.  The redirect shows up when phosphor-logging is built as a subproject so there is no need to check it in here.

Agree with Matt.  This isn't a direct dependency for entity-manager so you shouldn't include it as a wrap file here.

dbus-sensors has a `wrap-redirect` file for PDI and I would expect this repo to do the same (unless it were using PDI directly).


```
$ cat phosphor-dbus-interfaces.wrap                                               
[wrap-redirect]
filename = phosphor-logging/subprojects/phosphor-dbus-interfaces.wrap
```

Mhm ok, i think i figured it out now. The
```
subprojects/phosphor-dbus-interfaces.wrap  
```

is auto-generated by meson, and not upstream in dbus-sensors.
meson errors out when this wrap-redirect is provided and the subproject it references is not downloaded yet.

You're doing a lot more than that, so maybe something more along the lines of:  use lg2 for debug statements.

At some point it'd be good to get rid of all the std::cerr calls and just use lg2 for those as well.
Done
All of these that just print bytes may be more readable by using lg2::hex to print them in hex.  Also I'm not sure even how it is you'd need a cast, I don't think lg2 would try to convert to a char.
Done
This isn't a particularly useful log.  Can you add some text?
Done
oh, sorry, I should have mentioned this one and the below ones too, that the cast isn't needed anymore.  I fine either way on if they are printed in hex or not.
Suggest hex to match raw blockData from 652.
Done
